f7254-5e6a-9a28-ba23-d4125f4433f8"}, "input": {"input": ["地塞米松:地塞米松是一种糖皮质激素，可能引发精神症状，特别是在中枢神经系统兴奋性提高的情况下", "可的松:可的松是一种糖皮质激素，可能引发精神症状，但可能性低于地塞米松", "泼尼松:泼尼松是一种糖皮质激素，可能引发精神症状，但可能性低于地塞米松和可的松", "氢化可的松:氢化可的松是一种糖皮质激素，可能引发精神症状，但可能性低于地塞米松、可的松和泼尼松", "烟碱胆碱能受体:", "DEXAMETHASONE:Dexamethasone is a type of corticosteroid that can cause psychiatric symptoms such as insomnia, euphoria, irritability, and in severe cases, hallucinations and delusions. It is known to increase the excitability of the central nervous system, leading to these symptoms within days or up to two months of use.", "SYSTEMIC LUPUS ERYTHEMATOSUS:Systemic Lupus Erythematosus is an autoimmune disease that can cause psychiatric symptoms, especially during active phases. It can be challenging to differentiate whether these symptoms are due to the disease itself or the use of corticosteroids in treatment.", "ISONIAZID:Isoniazid is a primary drug used to treat tuberculosis. It can cause adverse effects such as peripheral neuropathy, dizziness, insomnia, and in high doses, it may lead to optic neuritis, seizures, and psychiatric symptoms due to vitamin B6 deficiency.", "ATROPINE:Atropine is a medication primarily known for its role in treating certain types of poisoning by blocking the effects of acetylcholine. It functions as an M-cholinergic receptor antagonist, which means it inhibits the action of acetylcholine at muscarinic receptors. While it is effective in counteracting poisoning, Atropine can also have significant effects on the central nervous system. These effects may include psychiatric symptoms such as excitement, agitation, and hallucinations. In severe cases, the use of Atropine can lead to more serious conditions like delirium and coma. Thus, while Atropine is a valuable therapeutic agent, its potential impact on the central nervous system necessitates careful monitoring and administration.", "ANTI-COLD MEDICATIONS:Anti-cold medications, which often contain ingredients like amantadine, pseudoephedrine, and chlorpheniramine, can cause acute psychiatric symptoms such as sleep disturbances, anxiety, hallucinations, and in severe cases, delirium due to their effects on dopamine and norepinephrine systems."], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-v3"}}}